cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM

This paper is about a new algorithm for video object tracking using convolutional neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of parametric gating functions to control the depth of the convolutional feature extractor, which is a machine learning technique, so it is also likely to be categorized as cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a new approach to balancing computational cost and tracking error, which is a form of optimization, so it could also be categorized as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the use of the proposed algorithm for robotics applications, which could lead to it being categorized as cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper is about video tracking, which is a multimedia application, so it could also be categorized as cs.MM (Multimedia).
